  "prompt": "Why do I have black lines on my teeth?",
  "response": "Black lines on teeth can be caused by several factors:\n\n1. Tartar or calculus buildup\n- Dark deposits at the gum line\n- Requires professional dental cleaning\n\n2. Tooth decay or cavities\n- Black or dark brown spots indicating tooth damage\n- Needs dental treatment\n\n3. Staining from food and drinks\n- Coffee, tea, red wine, and certain foods can cause discoloration\n- Can often be addressed through professional cleaning or whitening\n\n4. Smoking or tobacco use\n- Nicotine and tar can cause dark stains\n- Quitting can help improve tooth appearance\n\n5. Old dental fillings\n- Metal or amalgam fillings can appear dark or create a dark line\n- May need replacement with modern tooth-colored fillings\n\n6. Certain medications\n- Some medications can cause tooth discoloration\n\n7. Poor oral hygiene\n- Inadequate brushing and flossing can lead to plaque and stain buildup\n\n8. Aging\n- Teeth naturally darken over time\n\nRecommendation: Consult a dentist for a professional evaluation to determine the specific cause and appropriate treatment for your black tooth lines.",
